        <remarks>
          <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 It is often useful to be able to return a Task from a <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601>, where the inner Task represents work done as part of the outer <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601>. However, doing so results in a `Task<Task>` (C#) or `Task (Of Task)` (Visual Basic), which, if not dealt with carefully, could produce unexpected behavior. Unwrap solves this problem by creating a proxy Task that represents the entire asynchronous operation of such a task.  
  
   
  
## Examples  
